# ConfigLoaderSystem

## Purpose
One-shot initialization system. On the first frame, reads `Assets/Engine/Config.json` and creates
EngineConfigSingletonComponent with the UUIDs of the default quad shader, text shader, and font, plus
the master/sound/music audio volumes (optional keys; default to full volume when absent).
No-op on all subsequent frames (presence check guards early exit).

## Savedata Override
The engine config may declare a `savedataPath` entry pointing at the SaveData folder (a sibling of
Data, `../SaveData` from the working directory). After seeding the component from the engine config,
the system reads `<savedataPath>/Config.json` if it exists and overlays its entries on top — every
field is optional, so a key present in the savedata config overrides the engine value while absent
keys keep the engine value. When `savedataPath` is missing or the savedata config file does not
exist, the engine config values stand unchanged. The savedata file is the place for user/persisted
overrides (e.g. adjusted audio volumes) that must survive without editing the shipped engine config.

## Input Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| EngineConfigSingletonComponent | read | Presence-check only; if present, system exits immediately |

## Output Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| EngineConfigSingletonComponent | add (deferred) | Created once from Config.json; contains default shader and font UUIDs and master/sound/music volumes |
